<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Flowering occurs from May to early September, and fruiting from August to October.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huan C. Wang, Shao Y. Liu &amp; Z. T. Ren" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hemilophia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hemilophia cardiocarpa" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cardiocarpa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Hemilophia cardiocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the Greek words &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">kardio</emphasis>
&quot; (heart) and &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">karpos</emphasis>
&quot; (fruit), referring to the fruit shape of this new species.
</paragraph>
